'''Biker Advanced Recon Commandos''', also referred to as '''BARC troopers''', were [[special forces]] [[clone trooper]]s of the [[Grand Army of the Republic]] that were trained to ride [[BARC speeder]]s across difficult terrain or dangerous battlegrounds. BARC [[trooper]]s were equipped with modified [[clone trooper armor]] that directed their attention forward to avoid distractions, which could be dangerous to them at high speeds. During the final days of the [[Clone Wars]], BARC troopers under the command of [[Jedi General]] [[Stass Allie]] and [[Clone Commander]] [[Neyo]] were present on the [[planet]] [[Saleucami]]. Whilst out on a [[speeder bike]] patrol, Neyo was issued [[Order 66]] by the [[Supreme Chancellor]] of the [[Galactic Republic]], [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]], which forced him to open fire on his superior. As a result Allie, like most of the other [[Jedi]] across [[the galaxy]], was [[Death|killed]] by the [[troop]]s.

==Description==
BARC [[trooper]]s were specialized [[Advanced Recon Commando|ARC]] troopers who were trained to pilot high speed [[BARC speeder]]s in combat.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> They were often assigned reconnaissance missions, but could also act as cavalry for their allies or as a vanguard for [[Advanced Recon Force trooper|ARF]] troopers or [[All Terrain Reconnaissance Transport|AT-RT]]s. BARC troopers excelled at high speeds and boasted they had the speediest reaction times in the clone army. BARC troopers were also skilled in armed and unarmed combat as well as military tactics.<ref name="Join the Battle">''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars: Character Encyclopedia - Join the Battle!]]''</ref> BARC troopers tended to get impatient while riding slower, conventional [[clone trooper]] craft, as they were trained to think and move quickly.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" />

==History==
[[File:BARCspeeder_DB.png|thumb|left|300px|BARC troopers control BARC speeders on the planet Saleucami.]]
Like most clone troopers,<ref name="clonetroopers">{{Databank|clone-troopers|Clone Troopers}}</ref> BARC troopers were 1.83 [[meter]]s or 6 [[Foot|feet]] tall.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> During the [[Clone Wars]], BARC troopers were used prominently on [[Christophsis]], [[Orto Plutonia]] and [[Kashyyyk]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> By the [[Standard year|year]] [[19 BBY]],<ref name="Galactic Atlas">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''</ref> BARC troopers in the [[91st Mobile Reconnaissance Corps]] were stationed on [[Saleucami]] during the [[Outer Rim Sieges]] of the [[Clone Wars]]. Whilst riding across the [[planet]]'s terrain on a [[BARC speeder]], [[Clone Commander]] [[Neyo]] was issued [[Order 66]] by [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]] of the [[Galactic Republic]].<ref name="Episode III" /> Forced to comply as a result of their [[behavioral modification biochip]]s,<ref name="Orders">{{TCW|Orders (episode)}}</ref> he and a wingman opened fire on [[Jedi General]] [[Stass Allie]]'s [[speeder]], destroying the vehicle and [[Death|killing]] the [[Jedi]].<ref name="Episode III" /> After carrying out Order 66, Commander Neyo and his troops would go on to serve the newly formed [[Galactic Empire]]<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> which succeeded the Republic following Order 66 and the outbreak of the [[Great Jedi Purge]], with the BARC troopers of the 91st Recon Corps proceeding to serve in the new [[Imperial Army]].<ref name="Grand Army Encyclopedia" />

==Equipment==
BARC troopers wore a modified variant of standard [[clone trooper armor]],<ref name="databank armor">{{Databank|clone-trooper-armor|Clone Trooper Armor}}</ref> with a helmet that was fitted with blinders to direct attention forward and minimize distractions,<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> that could be dangerous at high speeds.<ref name="databank armor" /> Clone troopers on BARC speeders in armor similar to, but not exactly the same<ref name="Obi-Wan 4">[[Obi-Wan 4|''Obi-Wan'' 4]]</ref> as that of Phase II era BARC troopers,<ref name="Episode III" /> were active within a [[Battle of Saleucami (Mekedrix)|battle on Saleucami]]<ref name="Obi-Wan 4" /> between [[21 BBY]] and [[20 BBY]].<ref name="Flashback Date">[[Obi-Wan 4|''Obi-Wan'' 4]] establishes that the [[Battle of Saleucami (Mekedrix)|battle of Saleucami]] that [[Mekedrix]] fought in took place after the [[Battle of Ryloth]], which ended in "[[Liberty on Ryloth]]," but before the [[Devaron massacre]], which occurred in "[[Monster]]." Per the reasoning [[Template:TCWcanondates|here]], the events of "Liberty on Ryloth" can be dated to [[21 BBY]], while the events of "Monster" can be dated to [[20 BBY]]. As such, the battle of Saleucami must occur between those two [[Standard year|years]].</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The image for BARC troopers in the reference book ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars: Character Encyclopedia - Join the Battle!]]'' shows [[Jesse]] on Saleucami while transporting a wounded [[Rex]]. However, while Jesse was later promoted to ARC trooper,<ref name="Join the Battle" /> he was never seen wearing BARC trooper armor. Rex, Jesse, [[Kix]] and [[Hardcase]] all piloted BARC speeders during the [[Battle of Saleucami]], but they were not BARC troopers themselves.<ref name="The Deserter">{{TCW|The Deserter}}</ref>

